---
title: Homelessness on the Rise in Hamilton County
url: http://citybeat.com/cincinnati/blog-5787-as_federal_funds_go_down_homelessness_goes_up.html
---

Since 2011 almost $1.5 million has been cut from federal funding for rental assistance for Hamilton County residents. The dramatic decrease has driven a plethora of residents out onto the streets in Cincinnati and across the country. The number of people homeless in Hamilton County jumped by more than 400 people since 2011.
